@startuml
title Golden Ticket — from DC compromise to persistent access

participant "Attacker" as ATK
participant "Domain Controller\n(LSASS / krbtgt)" as DC
participant "Workstation\n(attacker-controlled)" as WS
participant "Target service\n(e.g. file server)" as SVC

== One-time theft on the DC ==
ATK -> DC : privilege::debug
ATK -> DC : lsadump::lsa /inject /name:krbtgt
DC --> ATK : krbtgt NTLM/AES hash + domain SID

== Later, from anywhere ==
ATK -> WS : kerberos::golden\n(domain, SID, krbtgt hash,\nuser, id) /ptt
note over WS
  Forged TGT injected into the
  current session. No contact
  with the DC was needed to mint it.
end note
WS -> SVC : present forged TGT -> request service ticket
SVC -> DC : (normal Kerberos validation)
DC --> SVC : ticket valid (encrypted with krbtgt key)
SVC --> WS : access granted as the impersonated identity

note over ATK, SVC
  Persists until the krbtgt password
  is reset TWICE. A single reset is
  not enough (password history = 2).
end note
@enduml
